"""
================================================================================
QUANTUM HEDGE | Real-Time Options Cross-Greek Exposure Monitor
================================================================================
Purpose:
    A live, institutional-grade dashboard that visualizes dealer Gamma (GEX),
    Vanna (VEX), and Charm (CEX) exposure across the options chain.
    Understanding WHERE market makers are concentrated tells you where price
    will be ATTRACTED (pinned) or REPELLED (cascading trend).

Architecture - Three Decoupled Layers:
    1. DATA PIPELINE LAYER  -- Swappable provider classes (Schwab, Yahoo, Sim)
       Each provider returns a standardized DataFrame. The math engine never
       cares which source supplied the data -- total API independence.

    2. MATHEMATICAL ENGINE  -- Pure Black-Scholes Greeks (no API dependencies)
       OptionsMarketSimulator computes Delta, Gamma, Vanna, Charm, and all
       exposure metrics using fully vectorized NumPy operations.

    3. PRESENTATION LAYER   -- Plotly Dash interactive dashboard
       Reactive callback system re-renders charts and metrics on every tick.

Key Concepts:
    GEX (Gamma Exposure):
        How many dollars market makers must buy/sell per 1% spot move to stay
        delta-neutral. Positive GEX = dealers BUY dips, SELL rallies (pin).
        Negative GEX = dealers CHASE momentum (volatility amplification).

    VEX (Vanna Exposure):
        How much dealer delta changes per 1% absolute shift in implied vol.
        Critical during vol crush events (e.g., post-earnings IV collapse).

    CEX (Charm Exposure):
        Passive daily delta decay -- how much dealer hedges "bleed" as time
        passes. Important heading into weekly or monthly expirations.

    Gamma Flip Level:
        The exact price where NET GEX crosses zero. Above = Long Gamma regime
        (mean-reverting). Below = Short Gamma regime (trend-following, volatile).
================================================================================
"""

